sin.T_in_internal.comment: Needed to connect to conditional connector

sin.X_in_internal[1].comment: Needed to connect to conditional connector

sin.p_in_internal.comment: Needed to connect to conditional connector

sin.ports[1].h_outflow.comment: Specific thermodynamic enthalpy close to the connection point if m_flow < 0

sou.T_in_internal.comment: Needed to connect to conditional connector

sou.X_in_internal[1].comment: Needed to connect to conditional connector

sou.p_in_internal.comment: Needed to connect to conditional connector

sou.ports[1].h_outflow.comment: Specific thermodynamic enthalpy close to the connection point if m_flow < 0

valLin.dp.comment: Pressure difference between port_a and port_b

valLin.k.comment: Flow coefficient of valve and pipe in series, k=m_flow/sqrt(dp), with unit=(kg.m)^(1/2).

valLin.m_flow.comment: Mass flow rate from port_a to port_b (m_flow > 0 is design flow direction)

valLin.phi.comment: Ratio actual to nominal mass flow rate of valve, phi=Kv(y)/Kv(y=1)

valLin.Kv_SI.comment: Flow coefficient for fully open valve in SI units, Kv=m_flow/sqrt(dp) [kg/s/(Pa)^(1/2)]

valLin._dp_start.comment: Start value for dp, used to avoid a warning if not set in dp, and to avoid dp.start in parameter window

valLin._m_flow_start.comment: Start value for m_flow, used to avoid a warning if not set in m_flow, and to avoid m_flow.start in parameter window

valLin.deltaM.comment: Fraction of nominal flow rate where linearization starts, if y=1

valLin.dpFixed_nominal.comment: Pressure drop of pipe and other resistances that are in series

valLin.dpValve_nominal.comment: Nominal pressure drop of fully open valve, used if CvData=Buildings.Fluid.Types.CvTypes.OpPoint

valLin.dp_nominal.comment: Pressure drop at nominal mass flow rate

valLin.dp_nominal_pos.comment: Absolute value of nominal pressure difference

valLin.eta_default.comment: Dynamic viscosity, used to compute transition to turbulent flow regime

valLin.kFixed.comment: Flow coefficient of fixed resistance that may be in series with valve, k=m_flow/sqrt(dp), with unit=(kg.m)^(1/2).

valLin.m_flow_nominal_pos.comment: Absolute value of nominal flow rate

valLin.m_flow_small.comment: Small mass flow rate for regularization of zero flow

valLin.rhoStd.comment: Inlet density for which valve coefficients are defined

valLin.riseTime.comment: Rise time of the filter (time to reach 99.6 % of an opening step)

y.duration.comment: Duration of ramp (= 0.0 gives a Step)

y.startTime.comment: Output y = offset for time < startTime

valLin.init.comment: Type of initialization (no init/steady state/initial state/initial output)

sin.use_C_in.comment: Get the trace substances from the input connector

sin.use_T_in.comment: Get the temperature from the input connector

sin.use_X_in.comment: Get the composition (all fractions) from the input connector

sin.use_Xi_in.comment: Get the composition (independent fractions) from the input connector

sin.use_p_in.comment: Get the pressure from the input connector

sin.verifyInputs.comment: Set to true to stop the simulation with an error if the medium temperature is outside its allowable range

sou.use_C_in.comment: Get the trace substances from the input connector

sou.use_T_in.comment: Get the temperature from the input connector

sou.use_X_in.comment: Get the composition (all fractions) from the input connector

sou.use_Xi_in.comment: Get the composition (independent fractions) from the input connector

sou.use_p_in.comment: Get the pressure from the input connector

sou.verifyInputs.comment: Set to true to stop the simulation with an error if the medium temperature is outside its allowable range

valLin.allowFlowReversal.comment: = false to simplify equations, assuming, but not enforcing, no flow reversal

valLin.casePreInd.comment: In case of PressureIndependent the model I/O is modified

valLin.from_dp.comment: = true, use m_flow = f(dp) else dp = f(m_flow)

valLin.linearized.comment: = true, use linear relation between m_flow and dp for any flow rate

valLin.show_T.comment: = true, if actual temperature at port is computed

valLin.use_inputFilter.comment: = true, if opening is filtered with a 2nd order CriticalDamping filter

sin.checkAirPressure.comment: Evaluates to true if the pressure should be checked

sin.checkWaterPressure.comment: Evaluates to true if the pressure should be checked

sou.checkAirPressure.comment: Evaluates to true if the pressure should be checked

sou.checkWaterPressure.comment: Evaluates to true if the pressure should be checked

sin.ports.1.h_outflow.$pDERA.dummyVarA.comment: Specific thermodynamic enthalpy close to the connection point if m_flow < 0

sou.ports.1.h_outflow.$pDERA.dummyVarA.comment: Specific thermodynamic enthalpy close to the connection point if m_flow < 0

valLin.k.$pDERA.dummyVarA.comment: Flow coefficient of valve and pipe in series, k=m_flow/sqrt(dp), with unit=(kg.m)^(1/2).

valLin.m_flow.$pDERA.dummyVarA.comment: Mass flow rate from port_a to port_b (m_flow > 0 is design flow direction)

valLin.phi.$pDERA.dummyVarA.comment: Ratio actual to nominal mass flow rate of valve, phi=Kv(y)/Kv(y=1)

equation: assert(sin.p_in_internal > 10000.0, "In TwoWayValve.sin: The parameter value p=" + String(sin.p_in_internal, 6, 0, true) + " is low for water. This is likely an error.");
assert(sou.p_in_internal > 10000.0, "In TwoWayValve.sou: The parameter value p=" + String(sou.p_in_internal, 6, 0, true) + " is low for water. This is likely an error.");
if time < 0.0 then 0.0 else if time < 1.0 then time else 1.0
assert(y.duration >= 0.0, "Variable violating min constraint: 0.0 <= y.duration, has value: " + String(y.duration, "g"));
assert(valLin.kFixed >= 0.0, "Variable violating min constraint: 0.0 <= valLin.kFixed, has value: " + String(valLin.kFixed, "g"));
assert(valLin.l >= 1e-10 and valLin.l <= 1.0, "Variable violating min/max constraint: 1e-10 <= valLin.l <= 1.0, has value: " + String(valLin.l, "g"));
assert(valLin.dpFixed_nominal >= 0.0, "Variable violating min constraint: 0.0 <= valLin.dpFixed_nominal, has value: " + String(valLin.dpFixed_nominal, "g"));

assert(valLin.init >= Modelica.Blocks.Types.Init.NoInit and valLin.init <= Modelica.Blocks.Types.Init.InitialOutput, "Variable violating min/max constraint: Modelica.Blocks.Types.Init.NoInit <= valLin.init <= Modelica.Blocks.Types.Init.InitialOutput, has value: " + String(valLin.init, "d"));
assert(valLin.rhoStd >= 0.0, "Variable violating min constraint: 0.0 <= valLin.rhoStd, has value: " + String(valLin.rhoStd, "g"));
assert(valLin.dpValve_nominal >= 0.0, "Variable violating min constraint: 0.0 <= valLin.dpValve_nominal, has value: " + String(valLin.dpValve_nominal, "g"));

assert(valLin.CvData >= Buildings.Fluid.Types.CvTypes.OpPoint and valLin.CvData <= Buildings.Fluid.Types.CvTypes.Av, "Variable violating min/max constraint: Buildings.Fluid.Types.CvTypes.OpPoint <= valLin.CvData <= Buildings.Fluid.Types.CvTypes.Av, has value: " + String(valLin.CvData, "d"));
assert(valLin.eta_default >= 0.0, "Variable violating min constraint: 0.0 <= valLin.eta_default, has value: " + String(valLin.eta_default, "g"));

assert(valLin.sta_default.T >= 1.0 and valLin.sta_default.T <= 10000.0, "Variable violating min/max constraint: 1.0 <= valLin.sta_default.T <= 10000.0, has value: " + String(valLin.sta_default.T, "g"));

assert(valLin.sta_default.p >= 0.0 and valLin.sta_default.p <= 100000000.0, "Variable violating min/max constraint: 0.0 <= valLin.sta_default.p <= 100000000.0, has value: " + String(valLin.sta_default.p, "g"));
assert(valLin.m_flow_turbulent >= 0.0, "Variable violating min constraint: 0.0 <= valLin.m_flow_turbulent, has value: " + String(valLin.m_flow_turbulent, "g"));
assert(valLin.m_flow_small >= 0.0, "Variable violating min constraint: 0.0 <= valLin.m_flow_small, has value: " + String(valLin.m_flow_small, "g"));
assert(sou.T >= 1.0 and sou.T <= 10000.0, "Variable violating min/max constraint: 1.0 <= sou.T <= 10000.0, has value: " + String(sou.T, "g"));
assert(sou.p >= 0.0 and sou.p <= 100000000.0, "Variable violating min/max constraint: 0.0 <= sou.p <= 100000000.0, has value: " + String(sou.p, "g"));
assert(sou.X[1] >= 0.0 and sou.X[1] <= 1.0, "Variable violating min/max constraint: 0.0 <= sou.X[1] <= 1.0, has value: " + String(sou.X[1], "g"));

assert(sou.flowDirection >= Modelica.Fluid.Types.PortFlowDirection.Entering and sou.flowDirection <= Modelica.Fluid.Types.PortFlowDirection.Bidirectional, "Variable violating min/max constraint: Modelica.Fluid.Types.PortFlowDirection.Entering <= sou.flowDirection <= Modelica.Fluid.Types.PortFlowDirection.Bidirectional, has value: " + String(sou.flowDirection, "d"));
assert(sin.T >= 1.0 and sin.T <= 10000.0, "Variable violating min/max constraint: 1.0 <= sin.T <= 10000.0, has value: " + String(sin.T, "g"));
assert(sin.p >= 0.0 and sin.p <= 100000000.0, "Variable violating min/max constraint: 0.0 <= sin.p <= 100000000.0, has value: " + String(sin.p, "g"));
assert(sin.X[1] >= 0.0 and sin.X[1] <= 1.0, "Variable violating min/max constraint: 0.0 <= sin.X[1] <= 1.0, has value: " + String(sin.X[1], "g"));

assert(sin.flowDirection >= Modelica.Fluid.Types.PortFlowDirection.Entering and sin.flowDirection <= Modelica.Fluid.Types.PortFlowDirection.Bidirectional, "Variable violating min/max constraint: Modelica.Fluid.Types.PortFlowDirection.Entering <= sin.flowDirection <= Modelica.Fluid.Types.PortFlowDirection.Bidirectional, has value: " + String(sin.flowDirection, "d"));

assert(sin.ports[1].h_outflow >= -10000000000.0 and sin.ports[1].h_outflow <= 10000000000.0, "Variable violating min/max constraint: -10000000000.0 <= sin.ports[1].h_outflow <= 10000000000.0, has value: " + String(sin.ports[1].h_outflow, "g"));

assert(sou.ports[1].h_outflow >= -10000000000.0 and sou.ports[1].h_outflow <= 10000000000.0, "Variable violating min/max constraint: -10000000000.0 <= sou.ports[1].h_outflow <= 10000000000.0, has value: " + String(sou.ports[1].h_outflow, "g"));

assert(valLin.m_flow >= -9.999999999999999e+59 and valLin.m_flow <= 100000.0, "Variable violating min/max constraint: -9.999999999999999e+59 <= valLin.m_flow <= 100000.0, has value: " + String(valLin.m_flow, "g"));
assert(valLin.k >= 1e-60, "Variable violating min constraint: 1e-60 <= valLin.k, has value: " + String(valLin.k, "g"));
assert(y.y >= 0.0 and y.y <= 1.0, "Variable violating min/max constraint: 0.0 <= y.y <= 1.0, has value: " + String(y.y, "g"));
